(1)
Gansevoort Market Stand, northern part, from Washington Street to Tenth Avenue, view north. This view shows the loft buildings on the west side of Washington Street, from Little West 12th to 13th Streets, which will have to be demolished in 1931. April 3, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, from the ground, two and a half years later, after demolition of 41-49 Little West 12th Street at the N.W. corner of Washington Street.
December 3, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same as No. 1, and showing a further view northward on Eleventh Ave.
April 3, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
